{{setTitle     "Get Started"}}
{{setSubTitle  "Start your next web project with Pure."}}
{{setActiveNav "start"}}
{{setLoadYUI   true}}
{{addLocalCSS  "/css/start.css"}}
{{addLocalJS   "/js/start.js"}}


{{> header}}

<div class="content">
    {{sectionHeading "Add Pure to Your Page"}}

    <p>
        You can add Pure to your page via Yahoo's free CDN. Just add the following {{code "<link>"}} element into your page's {{code "<head>"}}, before your project's stylesheets.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="is-code-full">
  {{#code wrap=true}}
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="http://yui.yahooapis.com/pure/{{pure.version}}/pure-min.css">
  {{/code}}
</div>

<div class="content">
    <aside>
        <p>
            Alternatively, you can <a href="https://github.com/yui/pure-release/archive/v{{pure.version}}.zip">download Pure</a>, or <a href="{{pathTo 'customize'}}">check out other CDNs</a> that host Pure.
        </p>
    </aside>

    {{sectionHeading "Add the Viewport Meta Tag"}}

    <p>
        The viewport {{code "meta"}} tag lets you control the the width and scale of the viewport on mobile browsers. Since we're building a responsive website, we want the width to be equal to the device's native width. Add this into your page's {{code "<head>"}}.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="is-code-full">
  {{#code wrap=true}}
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  {{/code}}
</div>

<div class="content">
    {{sectionHeading "Understand Pure Grids"}}

    <h3>Default Grids</h3>
    <p>
        Pure's grid system is very simple. You create a row by using the {{code ".pure-g"}} class, and create columns within that row by using the {{code "pure-u-*"}} classes.
    </p>

    <p>Here's a grid with three columns:</p>

  {{#code}}
    {{> grids/intro}}
  {{/code}}
</div>

<div class="grids-example">
    {{> grids/intro}}
</div>

<div class="content">
    <h3>Responsive Grids</h3>
    <p>
        Pure Grids can be extended to become a mobile-first responsive grid system. You're able to customize the grid by specifying media query breakpoints and grid classnames. You can <a href="#cols">customize grids below</a>, but let's start off with an example.
    </p>

    <p>
        Let's say that you specified the following grid:
    </p>

    <table class="pure-table pure-table-bordered">
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th class="th-highlight">Key</th>
                <th class="th-highlight">Media Query</th>
                <th>Class name</th>
                <th>Behavior</th>
        </thead>

        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td class="td-highlight">None</td>
                <td class="td-highlight">None</td>
                <td>{{code ".pure-u-*"}}</td>
                <td>Applies all the time</td>
            </tr>
            {{#each gridUnits}}
            <tr>
                <td class="td-highlight">{{code @key}}</td>
                <td class="td-highlight">
                    <code>@media {{this.type}} and ({{this.expressions.0.modifier}}-{{this.expressions.0.feature}}: {{this.expressions.0.value}})</code>
                </td>
                <td><code>.pure-u-{{@key}}-*</code></td>
                <td>Applies for â‰¥ {{this.expressions.0.value}} screens</td>
            </tr>
            {{/each}}
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>
        Here's an example of what you'd be able to do. Try resizing your screen to see how the grid responds.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="grids-example">
{{> grids/responsive}}
</div>

<div class="content">

    <p>
        The {{code "grid.css"}} that powers the example above is <a href="/start/?med=48em&lrg=60em#css">available here</a>. You can copy and paste it, or modify the keys and media query breakpoints to create your own custom responsive grid!
    </p>
</div>

